    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Feb 13./80</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                    
<p>I thank you heartily for your <hi rend="underline">most</hi> kind letter.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I write now merely to say that April 10<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> on the Epitaph is a dreadful mistake, made by the copyist, &amp; I cannot think how I overlooked it, but I very often overlook errata.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1"><ref target="./DCP-LETT-12469.xml">Letter from Ernst Krause, 10 February 1880</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">CD had not noticed the error in <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2365.xml"><hi rend="italic">Erasmus Darwin</hi></ref>, p. 127 (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12469.xml">letter from Ernst Krause, 10 February 1880</ref> and n. 3).</note>
        </div>
        
    
        
